      "text": "The first step is to generate some polygons. The simplest approach would be to use a hexagonal grid and perturb it a bit to make it look irregular. This works (and the techniques on this page will work if you use a perturbed grid), but I wanted something even less regular than that, so I picked random points and generated Voronoi polygons, which are used for lots of things, including maps. The Voronoi wiki is incomplete but has some useful background. I’m using nodename’s as3delaunay library, which has an implementation of Fortune’s Algorithm."
